  "response": "\"Blonde Mongolia\" likely refers to a misconception or miswording, as there's no specific group known by this exact term. If you're referring to individuals of Mongolian descent with blonde hair, that would indeed be rare due to genetic factors. \n\nMongolia is primarily inhabited by people of East Asian descent, and the most common hair color is black or dark brown. Blonde hair is a result of different genetic variations, which are less common among East Asian populations. People of Mongolian descent living in America generally reflect these genetic traits. \n\nIf you meant something else by \"Blonde Mongolia,\" please provide more context for clarity.",
